---
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import GlowLine from '../../components/GlowLine';
import BatteryHistoryBriefing from '../../components/basics/briefings/BatteryHistoryBriefing';
import InsideTheCellBriefing from '../../components/basics/briefings/InsideTheCellBriefing';
import PriceCrashBriefing from '../../components/basics/briefings/PriceCrashBriefing';
import BatteryChemistryWorkbench from '../../components/basics/labs/BatteryChemistryWorkbench';
import BatteryLifecycleSimulator from '../../components/basics/labs/BatteryLifecycleSimulator';
import UpcomingBatteryTech from '../../components/basics/labs/UpcomingBatteryTech';
import { url } from '../../utils/url';

const sections = [
  { id: 'history', title: 'Battery History' },
  { id: 'inside-the-cell', title: 'Inside the Cell' },
  { id: 'price-crash', title: 'The Price Crash' },
  { id: 'chemistry-workbench', title: 'Chemistry Workbench', interactive: true },
  { id: 'lifecycle', title: 'Lifecycle Simulator', interactive: true },
  { id: 'whats-next', title: "What's Next" },
];
---

<ContentLayout
  title="How Batteries Work"
  description="From Volta's pile to grid-scale storage — how lithium-ion batteries work, why they got so cheap, and what comes next."
  sections={sections}
>

<h1>How Batteries Work</h1>

<p class="text-xl" style="color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 600px;">
  From Volta's pile to grid-scale storage — how lithium-ion batteries work,
  why they got so cheap, and what comes next.
</p>

<noscript>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-lg my-6" style="background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-surface-light);">
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">
      This page contains interactive diagrams and simulations that require JavaScript.
      Please enable JavaScript to experience the full content.
    </p>
  </div>
</noscript>

<div class="my-8">
  <GlowLine client:visible />
</div>

<!-- Briefing 1: Battery History Timeline -->

<h2 id="history">From Volta to the Grid</h2>

<p>
  The battery is older than you think. Alessandro Volta built the first one in 1800 — a stack of
  zinc and copper discs separated by brine-soaked cloth. It took nearly two centuries to get from
  that crude pile to the lithium-ion cells that power everything from phones to grid-scale storage.
</p>

<div class="my-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden" style="background: var(--color-bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--color-surface-light); padding: 16px;">
  <BatteryHistoryBriefing client:visible />
</div>

<p>
  The 2019 Nobel Prize in Chemistry went to Goodenough, Whittingham, and Yoshino — the three
  scientists whose work made lithium-ion batteries possible. Today, grid-scale battery installations
  are measured in gigawatt-hours.
</p>

<!-- Briefing 2: Inside the Cell -->

<h2 id="inside-the-cell">Inside the Cell</h2>

<p>
  Every lithium-ion cell has the same basic structure: two electrodes (anode and cathode) separated
  by an electrolyte. During charging, lithium ions migrate from cathode to anode. During discharging,
  they flow back — and electrons take the external circuit, powering whatever is connected.
</p>

<div class="my-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden" style="background: var(--color-bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--color-surface-light); padding: 16px;">
  <InsideTheCellBriefing client:visible />
</div>

<p>
  Lithium is the lightest metal and has the highest electrochemical potential of any element. That
  combination makes it ideal for batteries — more energy per gram than any alternative.
</p>

<!-- Briefing 3: The Price Crash -->

<h2 id="price-crash">The Price Crash</h2>

<p>
  In 2010, a lithium-ion battery pack cost $1,100 per kilowatt-hour. By 2023, that number had
  dropped to $139 — an 89% reduction in 13 years. This is one of the fastest cost declines in
  the history of energy technology.
</p>

<div class="my-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden" style="background: var(--color-bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--color-surface-light); padding: 16px;">
  <PriceCrashBriefing client:visible />
</div>

<p>
  Three forces drove the crash: gigafactory-scale manufacturing, reduced dependence on expensive
  cobalt, and intense competition — especially from Chinese manufacturers like CATL and BYD.
  Projections suggest pack prices could reach $50-80/kWh by 2030.
</p>

<div class="my-8">
  <GlowLine client:visible />
</div>

<!-- Lab 1: Chemistry Workbench -->

<h2 id="chemistry-workbench">Chemistry Workbench</h2>

<p>
  Not all lithium-ion batteries are the same. The cathode chemistry determines the battery's
  character — its energy density, cycle life, safety, and cost. Compare four major chemistries
  and see why different applications choose different batteries.
</p>

<div class="my-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden p-4 scroll-mt-20" style="background: var(--color-bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--color-surface-light);">
  <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
    <div class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase" style="color: var(--color-text);">BATTERY CHEMISTRY RADAR</div>
    <span
      class="font-mono text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
      style="background: rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.1); color: var(--color-primary); border: 1px solid rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.2);"
    >
      Interactive
    </span>
  </div>
  <BatteryChemistryWorkbench client:visible />
  <div class="text-xs mt-3" style="color: var(--color-text-dim);">
    Select a chemistry to see its radar profile. Use Compare mode to overlay two chemistries.
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Lab 2: Lifecycle Simulator -->

<h2 id="lifecycle">Battery Lifecycle Simulator</h2>

<p>
  How long does a battery last? It depends on how you use it. Deeper discharges, faster charging,
  higher temperatures, and more frequent cycling all accelerate degradation. Adjust the parameters
  to see how different usage patterns affect battery lifespan.
</p>

<div class="my-8 rounded-lg overflow-hidden p-4 scroll-mt-20" style="background: var(--color-bg-alt); border: 1px solid var(--color-surface-light);">
  <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
    <div class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase" style="color: var(--color-text);">LIFECYCLE SIMULATOR</div>
    <span
      class="font-mono text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
      style="background: rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.1); color: var(--color-primary); border: 1px solid rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.2);"
    >
      Interactive
    </span>
  </div>
  <BatteryLifecycleSimulator client:visible />
  <div class="text-xs mt-3" style="color: var(--color-text-dim);">
    Try the presets to see typical usage patterns, or adjust sliders manually. The red line marks 80% State of Health — the industry standard for "end of life."
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Lab 3: What's Next -->

<h2 id="whats-next">What's Next</h2>

<p>
  Lithium-ion dominates today, but several next-generation technologies are closing in. Some
  promise higher density, others lower cost, and a few could eliminate lithium entirely.
</p>

<div class="my-8">
  <UpcomingBatteryTech client:visible />
</div>

<!-- Footer -->

<div class="my-8">
  <GlowLine client:visible />
</div>

<div class="my-8 p-6 rounded-lg no-arrow" style="background: rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.15);">
  <div class="font-mono text-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-primary); letter-spacing: 0.08em;">CONTINUE</div>
  <a href={url("/basics/beyond-lithium-ion")} class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">
    Beyond Lithium-Ion
  </a>
  <div class="text-sm mt-1" style="color: var(--color-text-dim);">
    Long-duration storage, flow batteries, compressed air, and the technologies that will shape the grid of 2030.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="my-4 p-4 rounded-lg no-arrow" style="background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-surface-light);">
  <div class="font-mono text-xs mb-1" style="color: var(--color-text-dim); letter-spacing: 0.08em;">GO DEEPER</div>
  <a href={url("/research/topics/electricity-pricing")} class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-primary);">
    Research: Electricity Pricing
  </a>
</div>

</ContentLayout>
